leadingComments.value:
*
 * adds a template to the template repository
 * depending on the template's file name,
 * it builds the repository recursively,
 * assuming the template filename follows
 * the following naming rules:
 *
 * ### Filename: 
 * 'nn-position-method.template'
 *
 * ### Meaning:
 * file-extension: '.template' used as filter criteria
 * delimiter: '-' to split the name into its logic parts
 *
 * ### Parts:
 * * nn: sequence for sorting filenames
 * * position: the position, at which the code will be injected
 * * method: the method name
 *
 * @example 00-header.template
 * @example 10-class.template
 * @example 11-methods-constructor.template
 * @example 30-methods-find.template
 * @example 70-methods-insert.template
 *
 * @example repository
 *  repository = {
 *    "header": <template source> 
 *    "class": <template source>
 *    "methods": {
 *      "constructor": <template source>,
 *      "authRole": <template source>,
 *      "findOneById": <template source>,
 *      "find": <template source>,
 *      ... : ...
 *      "insert": <template source>,
 *      "updateById": <template source>,
 *      "removeById": <template source>,
 *    }
 *  }
 *
 * @private
 * @param {string} key - current hierarchy level of the key
 * @param {string} source - template source code from template file
 * @return {object} repository_tree_part - a part of the repository tree
